The actual sandwich had 2 hard fried rubbery eggs, un-crisp limp bacon that tasted like turkey bacon,1 slice of American Cheese, and un- crispy toast with hard edges. I will definitely not be returning and I advise travellers not eat here. The staff were unhappy working there and you could definitely see and feel that.

Been here twice now and disappointed both times, neither time was it that busy either. 1st time, counter order, rude customer service and food order was a mess. Bagel was burnt and cheese was more in the wrapper than on the sandwich. I love Dunkin normally so thought they had an off day. 2nd and last time, only one person behind the counter seemed to understand or could communicate what was going on and he was very flippant and yelling at the ladies who worked there. I was picking up my and a friends mobile order. She put hers in before mine and it was simpler. Mine was done and I waited for hers for a while. When I was asked what I was waiting for they quickly threw her order together and handed it to me abruptly. When I got back she called to tell them that they got part of her order wrong (missing items) and they lied and said it was my fault. That I took the wrong order. Mind you, there were no other orders sitting around for me to take. I took what they shoved at me. My food was subpar at best. Coffee was good but my bagel was both burnt and under toasted at the same time. What?? Also tasted stale and rubbery. Coffee, sandwich and hasbrowns = $15 breakfast. That's way too much for what I got. With Starbucks, Royal Farms, and Burger King all nearby and closer to me than Dunkin, I will be going to them from now on. I am done with this shop.
